ngx_http_url_hash_module
-----------------------------------------------------

The ngx_http_url_hash_module module creates variable whose
values is the http 302 location depend on the hash of request
uri. It can be used with rewrite to implement simple load
balance.

Example Configuration
=====================

    url_hash $urlhash {
        backend     192.168.100.1;
        backend     192.168.100.2;
        backend     192.168.100.3:8080;
    }
    
    location / {
        rewrite ^/(.*) $urlhash redirect;
    }

Diretives
=========

syntax: url_hash $variable { ... }
default: --
context: http, server, location

The only supported parameter is:

backend
    host and port in HTTP 302 redirect location

